parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission's reverse gear can cause the vehicle to be unable to move in reverse, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle will not move in reverse
behaves as if it is in neutral
sudden loss of reverse gear without warning
no noise or motion when attempting to shift into reverse.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the differential sub-frame can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: Visible cracking of metal surrounding the area
driver's side rear bushing has pulled out of frame of car.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear subframe can cause the rear of the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents.
symptoms: Squeaking or creaking noises from the rear of the vehicle
metal on metal clunking noise
tearing or cracking of the subframe mounts
and loss of structural integrity.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential bushing can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Soft or spongy clutch pedal
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
and the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Takata Airbag Recall and Unintended Deployment
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended deployment of airbags can cause serious injuries, accidents, and even fatalities. The recall of Takata airbags has led to a shortage of replacement parts, leaving vehicle owners without a functioning airbag system.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the airbag deploys without a crash
the passenger airbag does not deploy in a crash
the driver's side airbag deploys inadvertedly
the airbag warning indicator illuminates on the instrument control panel.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag warning light stays on
the passenger airbag does not deploy in a crash
the airbag warning indicator illuminates on the instrument control panel.
